The Bigger Lesson
You are starting to see that "Modern" does not equal "Advanced."

Modern is often just "the latest trend."

Advanced is "a solution that has been refined over thousands of years."

By recognizing this—whether it’s in marriage, clothing, or the study of Sutras—you are decolonizing your own thinking. You are realizing that your culture didn't just "lack" modern technology; it was operating on a different, often more sophisticated, set of human-centered technologies all along.
